init_text: You're Barack Obama. 4 years into your retirement, you awake to find a letter with no return address on your bedside table. It reads "I hope you've had a chance to relax Barack...but pack your bags and call the number below. It's time to start the real job." Signed simply, "JFK."

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: He looks out the window and notices that two men in black suits are looking up at him.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: After a minute of searching, he finds a note in his suitcase that reads "There is no need to look any further.

actions.text: Obama jumps in the back and is driven to an abandoned warehouse.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: "Sorry about the theatrics Obama, but i don't like to be followed."

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: He tells him that he was not the only president who was apart of the society, but since his retirement, Obama is now being asked to join.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: JFK tells Obama that the society was started by his father and after the death of JFK, it fell on him to carry on the work.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: JFK goes on to tell Obama that the society is governed by a group of twelve men (all former presidents), he is one of them

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: JFK tells Obama that the first mission will be in four days time.
